update.description:
Hello :)

I updated models of TurtleBot3. This update excludes unused plugin for gazebo standalone source code.

TurtleBot3 House is new map for multiple TurtleBot3. I draw this using building editor.

![turtlebot3_house.png](https://bitbucket.org/repo/XXjgdKx/images/1235798448-turtlebot3_house.png)

![turtlebot3_house1.png](https://bitbucket.org/repo/XXjgdKx/images/3379847338-turtlebot3_house1.png)

First, Control TurtleBot3 by standalone gazebo plugin
Second, SLAM by multiple TurtleBot3 in TurtleBot3 House.

The code is uploaded [Github](https://github.com/ROBOTIS-GIT/turtlebot3_simulations)
and [wiki](http://emanual.robotis.com/docs/en/platform/turtlebot3/simulation/#simulation) will be updated

Thanks
Darby

content.raw:
It looks like this model has several nested models which are also found on the database. We could avoid duplication and instead of copying their description here, use the `<include>` tag, which takes the model and copies their links into this one.

For example:

~~~
<model name='turtlebot3_house'>
....
  <include>
    <uri>model://mailbox</uri>
    <pose>0.883462 -0.576236 0 0 0 -3.14159</pose>
  </include>
...
</model>
~~~
content.html:
It looks like this model has several nested models which are also found on the database. We could avoid duplication and instead of copying their description here, use the <include> tag, which takes the model and copies their links into this one.

For example:

<model name='turtlebot3_house'>
....
  <include>
    <uri>model://mailbox</uri>
    <pose>0.883462 -0.576236 0 0 0 -3.14159</pose>
  </include>
...
</model>

You're right. A turtlebot3_simulation pkg includes TB3 gazebo models(.sdf)
and it is same as i uploaded.

download .sdf using 'wget' command separetely.
But if this pull request is accepted, i would delete TB3 models(.sdf) in a
turtlebot3_simulation pkg.

Furthermore, older TB3 demos have been updating for synchronizing  every
TB3 model. We always keep in mind it when we develop code.

Because i didn't write down a model in CMakeLists, please inform to me when
you accept this request. Then, I will get new pull request including it.

Darby
content.html:
You're right. A turtlebot3_simulation pkg includes TB3 gazebo models(.sdf) and it is same as i uploaded. For now, user can use this to copy onto their gazebo model folder or download .sdf using 'wget' command separetely. But if this pull request is accepted, i would delete TB3 models(.sdf) in a turtlebot3_simulation pkg.

Furthermore, older TB3 demos have been updating for synchronizing every TB3 model. We always keep in mind it when we develop code.

Because i didn't write down a model in CMakeLists, please inform to me when you accept this request. Then, I will get new pull request including it.

Darby

content.raw: In general it's good to have these models more easily accessible. Will these models be useful without the ROS packages which include the drivers and plugins to operate them? Will there be tutorials for using them standalone? And looking forward at potential evolutions of the designs that might need to be versioned between rosdistros that would make this upstream hosting more challenging rather than continuing to distribute the models through their ROS packages where they can follow similar versioning release cycles?
